Here's the recommended implementation using **CommunityToolkit.Mvvm** (source-generated, AOT-safe):

**ViewModel:**

```csharp
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.ComponentModel;
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.Input;

public partial class ProductDetailViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _name = string.Empty;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private decimal _price;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isAvailable;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task LoadAsync()
    {
        // Replace with your actual data service call
        var product = await FetchProductAsync();
        Name = product.Name;
        Price = product.Price;
        IsAvailable = product.IsAvailable;
    }

    private async Task<(string Name, decimal Price, bool IsAvailable)> FetchProductAsync()
    {
        await Task.Delay(500); // simulate network
        return ("Widget", 29.99m, true);
    }
}
```

The source generator creates public `Name`, `Price`, `IsAvailable` properties with `PropertyChanged` notification, plus a `LoadCommand` (IAsyncRelayCommand) — all automatically.

**XAML page with compiled bindings:**

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels"
             x:DataType="vm:ProductDetailViewModel">

    <VerticalStackLayout Padding="16" Spacing="12">
        <Label Text="{Binding Name}" FontSize="24" />
        <Label Text="{Binding Price, StringFormat='Price: {0:C2}'}" />
        <Label Text="{Binding IsAvailable, StringFormat='In Stock: {0}'}" />
        <Button Text="Load Product"
                Command="{Binding LoadCommand}" />
        <ActivityIndicator IsRunning="{Binding LoadCommand.IsRunning}"
                           IsVisible="{Binding LoadCommand.IsRunning}" />
    </VerticalStackLayout>
</ContentPage>
```

**Key points:**

- `x:DataType` at the page root enables **compiled bindings** (8–20× faster, trimming-safe).
- `[RelayCommand]` on an `async Task` method auto-generates `LoadCommand` as an `IAsyncRelayCommand`, which exposes `IsRunning` for free — great for activity indicators.
- `PropertyChanged` is auto-marshalled to the UI thread, so assigning properties from the async method is safe.
- Add `<WarningsAsErrors>XC0022;XC0025</WarningsAsErrors>` to your `.csproj` to catch binding mistakes at build time.

**NuGet package required:** `CommunityToolkit.Mvvm` (≥ 8.2).
